summary.purpose: Defines the RuptelaEventEnum enumeration mapping Ruptela GPS device event names to their numeric event IDs.
summary.problem_solved: Provides a type-safe, self-documenting mapping between Ruptela hardware event codes and their semantic meaning, preventing hard-coded magic numbers in event-processing code.

exports.name: RuptelaEventEnum
exports.description_one_line: Numeric event IDs for Ruptela GPS device telemetry events

symbols.name: RuptelaEventEnum
symbols.description_one_line: Numeric event IDs for Ruptela GPS device telemetry events

details.what_it_does: Maps nine Ruptela GPS-tracker telemetry event types to their numeric IDs as defined by the Ruptela protocol. Members cover location updates (1) and paired ignition, engine, power-cut, and charging on/off events (2–9). Used by event-processing services to identify and route incoming device messages.

returns.description: One of the nine named numeric event codes.

minimal_correct.title: Match an incoming Ruptela event ID

extensive_correct.title: Switch on all Ruptela event types

incorrect.title: Using raw numbers instead of enum members
incorrect.why_incorrect: Magic numeric literals are unreadable and break silently if the Ruptela protocol ever renumbers events. Always use the enum member for type safety and searchability.
